Location. Located in London (Tottenham), The Fountain is close to White Hart Lane Stadium, Emirates Stadium, and Finsbury Park.

Also nearby are Alexandra Palace and William Morris Gallery. Hotel Features. This London hotel offers a restaurant and a bar/lounge.

Wireless Internet access is complimentary in public areas. Additional amenities include a nightclub, tour/ticket assistance, and a garden.

This is a smoke-free property. Guestrooms. The 9 guestrooms at The Fountain include coffee/tea makers and shared/communal kitchens.

Complimentary wireless high-speed Internet access is provided. Rooms are equipped with LCD TVs.
name: Fountain Hotel

description:
The Holland Court Hotel is a beautiful 3-star hotel set in a historic building in the centre of London's Kensington Olympia.

Guests at the Holland Court Hotel can enjoy attending an exhibition at the nearby Earls Court & Olympia Exhibition Centres, or go shopping at Westfield London Shopping Centre, also a stone's throw away.

Holland Park is within a short walk, while a longer stroll will take you to the famous Hyde Park. The Holland Court Hotel lies at elegant and historic Kensington end of the Holland Road, connecting Kensington and Shepherds Bush, two popular areas of London.

The Hotel is a short walk from Kensington Olympia Underground and Earls Court Underground Station and High Street Kensington Underground Station.

Heathrow Airport is within 25 minutes of the hotel, with direct access on the Piccadilly Line. London Victoria Train Station is only 2 stops away.
Offering 27 singles, doubles and triples, Holland Court Hotel stands out for its comfortable rooms and excellent customer service.

Guests can enjoy room amenities such as a TV (refundable deposit for the remote control applied), wireless internet access, heating a safe and a hairdryer.

All of the rooms have private bathrooms and tea and coffee making facilities. Communal facilities include a 24-hour reception desk, Wi-Fi in public areas, a safe and air conditioning.

The Holland Court Hotel provides a good location and accommodation in a typical Kensington building with simple yet homely interiors for a very comfortable stay.
A comfortable, historic base for the traveller in London, with free Wi-Fi and easy access to Earls Court and Olympia Exhibition Centres.
Hotel located on Holland Road in London.

Just a short walk away from Kensington Olympia Underground train station (tube).
The nearest railway station, London Victoria, is two tube stops away and Heathrow Airport can be reached in 25 minutes from the hotel.
name: Holland Court Hotel

description:
Free parking and simple, no-frills guest rooms with free Wi-Fi are offered by this budget guest house in East London.

There are two tube stations within a 12-minute walk offering fast, direct connections to central London.
There are 17 simply furnished guest rooms at the Lonsdale Lodge, all with private bathrooms, a TV, facilities for making tea and coffee and Wi-Fi service.

An inexpensive breakfast is available on request, and other amenities include a left luggage service and free private parking.
The guest house is located just two tube stops from Stratford, where you'll find the enormous Westfield shopping centre and the Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park and Stadium.

The tube also provides direct connections to Oxford Street and famous London sights such as St Paul's Cathedral.
Underground (Central line): Wanstead, 800 metres; Leytonstone, 1 kilometre.
Bus (various lines): 400 metres.
name: Lonsdale Lodge

description:
This city hotel is centrally located in the bustling metropolis of London. The hotel offers the ideal setting from which to enjoy the exciting nightlife scene, entertainment venues, exceptional shopping opportunities and exquisite dining options the city has to offer.

Guests will find themselves within easy access of the spectacular attractions this mesmerising city has to offer.

The hotel enjoys a stunning, Victorian architectural style allowing it to blend in seamlessly with its historical surroundings.

Guests are invited into the beautiful surroundings of the lobby which enjoys a minimalistic style. The guest rooms are tastefully decorated enjoying a cheerful style.

The rooms offer a welcoming escape away from the bustle of the city. |
name: Orchard Paddington Hotel

description:
Budget rooms with free Wi-Fi and shared kitchen facilities are on offer at this affordable hotel in East London, which is just two underground stops from Liverpool Street train station in the city's financial district.
The 3-star City View Hotel - Roman Road Market has 21 guest rooms, which are functionally decorated and equipped with en suite bathrooms, a flat-screen TV, and free Wi-Fi.

There is a shared kitchen available for the use of guests, as well as a TV lounge and laundry facilities.
The hotel is located very close to the popular Roman Road Market, where you can pick up everything from food to handmade crafts, and is only a 10-minute walk from the arty cafés and galleries of the vibrant Bethnal Green district.

Great public transport links mean you can be strolling down Oxford Street in the city centre in about 30 minutes.
Underground: Mile End (Central, Circle, District, Hammersmith & City lines), and Bow Road (Circle, District, Hammersmith & City lines), both 900 metres.
Bus: line 8, 25 metres.
Train: Bethnal Green, 900 metres.
name: City View Hotel - Roman Road Market

description:
Location. Located in London (Hammersmith and Fulham), Hotel 65 is close to Shepherd's Bush Empire, Hammersmith Apollo, and Portobello Road Market.

Also nearby are Kensington Palace and Craven Cottage Stadium. Hotel Features. Guests are served a complimentary breakfast each morning.

In addition to a safe deposit box at the front desk, Hotel 65 features a porter/bellhop. Wireless Internet access is complimentary in public areas.

This is a smoke-free property. Guestrooms. The 75 guestrooms at Hotel 65 include coffee/tea makers and hair dryers.

Complimentary wireless high-speed Internet access is provided. Rooms are equipped with LCD TVs with digital channels.

Bathrooms offer showers and complimentary toiletries. Housekeeping is offered daily.
name: Hotel 65

address: 365-367 Romford Rd, Forest Gate; E7 8AA London
description:
This budget hotel offers affordable accommodation and free parking in east London, just a 15-minute drive from the Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park.
The 1-star Hartley Hotel offers simply decorated guest rooms for between 1 and 5 guests, which all feature flat-screen TVs, Wi-Fi and heating.

Most rooms have shared bathrooms, although doubles and family rooms (for 5 guests) are available with en suite facilities.

A buffet breakfast is served each morning, and other services include a 24-hour reception desk and free private parking.
The hotel is located just a 10-minute walk from the West Ham United FC’s Upton Park stadium, and about a 10-minute drive from the Westfield Stratford City shopping centre.

There are direct trains (which take about 15 minutes) into central London from the nearby Forest Gate station, or you can hop on the tube at Upton Park.
Taxi: 50 metres.
Bus (various lines): opposite.
Underground: Upton Park, 1.4 kilometres.
Train: Forest Gate, 400 metres.
name: Hartley Hotel

description:
Handily located next to Paddington Station, this no-frills hotel right in the centre of London provides functional rooms at an affordable price.
There are 21 en suite rooms available at the Hyde Park Court Hotel, which are simply decorated and equipped with a TV, Wi-Fi and facilities for making tea and coffee.

A continental breakfast is served each morning, and the hotel also offers a 24-hour reception and a left-luggage office.

The owners also operate an Indian restaurant, which is just 2 minutes' walk from the hotel.
The hotel is just steps from Paddington station, which has handy tube links to the city centre as well as train services to Heathrow Airport.

The area enjoys plenty of shops and pubs and you can stroll to Hyde Park and Buckingham Palace in less than 15 minutes.
Metro: Paddington (District, Circle, Hammersmith & City lines, regional/national rail lines), 300 metres.
name: Hyde Park Court Hotel

description:
This affordable hotel is handily situated in east London, ideally placed for visiting The City, Docklands, the Olympic Park and the Westfield Stratford City shopping centre.
The century-old building retains its high ceilings and stucco decoration, and contains 27 cheerfully decorated single, double and triple rooms.

All have en suite bathrooms, flat-screen TV, and kettles. Services and amenities include Wi-Fi (extra charge), laundry service, DVD-hire, and a private car park (extra charge).
The Travel Inn is fantastically situated within walking distance of the Olympic Park.

It's handily placed for DLR and Underground services, and a direct bus departs every 5 minutes from right outside the hotel to Oxford Street in the city centre.

Whether you have business in The City, or want to catch a show in the West End, you can be in the heart of London in minutes.
Bus stop: opposite.
DLR: Stratford High Street, 600 metres.
Train station: Stratford International, 1.6 kilometres.
Underground: Stratford, 1.6 kilometres.
name: Travel Inn

description:
The 3-star Comfotel Blu Hotel is located in Shepherd's Bush, one of London's most vibrant neighbourhoods, and is handy for the Hammersmith HMV Apollo, the Westfield Shoopping Centre, and the Earls Court and Olympia conference centres.

There are 16 simple, attractively decorated en suite guest rooms, which can accommodate from 1 to 5 guests.

A full English breakfast is served in the breakfast room each morning. There is a 24-hour reception service.
The Comfotel Blu Hotel is within walking distance of Kensington High Street and Portobello Road market, and is close to the Craven Cottage Stadium and Stamford Bridge Stadium.

You can hop on the tube to reach central London and famous attractions like the London Eye and Buckingham Palace in just a few minutes.
Metro: Goldhawk Road, Circle, Distric & Hammersmith Line, 650 metres.
Bus: 150 metres.
Taxi rank: 650 metres.
Train: Paddington, 4.5 kilometres.
name: Comfotel Blu

description:
Budget-friendly hotel near Kensington Gardens Walk to Kensington Palace Budget-friendly Palace Court Hotel is located on Prince's Square in Bayswater, a quiet neighborhood in the heart of London.

Walk to Kensington Gardens in 5 minutes or Hyde Park in 15 minutes. It’s a 5-minute walk to Bayswater Tube Station.

Retail therapy Shoppers find Palace Court Hotel an ideal base. More than 100 restaurants, bars, and shops are within walking distance.

Whiteleys shopping center is an 8-minute walk, or hop on the Tube for a 15-minute journey to mega mall Westfield London.

Free breakfast and WiFi You can fill up on the free breakfast buffet while you read the newspaper or check your emails.

Need help booking a tour? The reception desk is open 24 hours and staff is happy to help with museum and tour tickets.

Free WiFi is also available at the reception desk. Clean and comfortable Make yourself comfortable in one of the recently renovated guestrooms.

Each is fully equipped with all the basics, including hair dryers and coffeemakers. Guests give high marks to polite staff.
name: Palace Court Hotel

description:
This 2-star hotel in central London is located 600 metres from the Olympia Exhibition Centre, and 1.4 kilometres from the Earl's Court Exhibition Centre, and offers simple, affordable rooms with Wi-Fi.
The Holland Inn Hotel has 26 functional en suite guest rooms, which are traditionally furnished and come with a TV, Wi-Fi (for an extra charge) and facilities for making tea and coffee.

The hotel has a 24-hour reception, laundry facilities and a left-luggage office.
The hotel is surrounded by a good choice of pubs and cafés, and is only a 10-minute walk to Shepherd's Bush tube station, a 2-minute walk to Kensington train station, and a 15-minute walk from the fashionable shops of High Street Kensington.

Elegant Knightsbridge, with its upmarket department stores, and Hyde Park are just 10 minutes away by bus.
Train: Kensington (Olympia), 300 metres.
Metro: Kensington (District Line), 300 metres.
Bus (various lines): opposite.
name: Holland Inn Hotel

address: 105 Godwin Rd, Forest Gate,; E7 0LW London
description:
Location. Located in London (Newham), Forest Gate Hotel is close to Wanstead Park, Boleyn Ground Stadium, and Ilford Golf Club.

Also nearby are Westfield Stratford City and Valentines Park. Hotel Features. The hotel offers a bar/lounge. A complimentary breakfast is available.

Wireless Internet access is complimentary in public areas. Additional amenities include a terrace, laundry facilities, and a garden.

The property has designated areas for smoking. Guestrooms. The 20 guestrooms at Forest Gate Hotel include coffee/tea makers and irons/ironing boards.

Guests can use the in-room complimentary wireless high-speed Internet access. Rooms are equipped with flat-screen TVs with pay movies.

Guests share bathrooms and amenities include complimentary toiletries. All units feature microwaves and refrigerators.

In addition, housekeeping is offered daily and amenities available on request include hair dryers.
name: Forest Gate Hotel

description:
Budget-friendly hotel near Paddington Station and Hyde Park Walk to Paddington At budget-friendly Norfolk Plaza Hotel, you're in an Edwardian style neighborhood right around the corner from Paddington Station, where you can jump on the Heathrow Express or the Tube.

For some green in the middle of London, Hyde Park is an 8-minute stroll from the hotel. Thrifty or upscale shops The famed Marble Arch is a 15-minute walk from the hotel.

If shopping is more your thing, you can hunt for bargains at nearby Church Street Market, or walk 20 minutes to the boutiques on Oxford Street.

Breakfast options You can start your day with a choice of classic Full English breakfast, continental breakfast, or buffet breakfast.

In addition to 2 lounges, this hotel also features a bar with a large screen TV – the perfect place to catch the game.

Simple and unpretentious Guestrooms are homey and simply furnished, offering all you need for a place to recharge after exploring London.

You can brew a cup of coffee or tea in your room before flipping through the satellite channels on your TV.
name: Norfolk Plaza Hotel

description:
Offering free Wi-Fi, this budget hotel in central London is conveniently located next to Paddington train station and only a 5-minute walk from Hyde Park.
The 2-star Seymour Hotel offers 54 no-frills, affordable guest rooms arranged on six floors of a Victorian townhouse (please note that there is no lift).

All rooms come with a private bathroom, free Wi-Fi, a TV with satellite channels and facilities for making tea and coffee.

The hotel provides a 24-hour reception and a left-luggage office.
The hotel is situated just 300 metres from Paddington train station, where you can take local and express trains to Heathrow Airport, as well as underground links to sights around the city.

Madame Tussauds, Marble Arch and Oxford Street can all be reached on foot in about 15 or 20 minutes, or else you could hop on a handy bus.
Taxi: opposite.
Bus: 160 metres.
Underground: Paddington, 300 metres.
Train: Paddington, 300 metres.
name: Seymour Hotel

description:
Location. Located in London (Camberwell), The New Dome Hotel is close to Brixton Market, Kennington Oval, and Imperial War Museum.

Also nearby are O2 Academy Brixton and London South Bank University. Hotel Features. Public areas are equipped with wireless Internet access (surcharges apply).

This is a smoke-free property. Guestrooms. Accommodations at The New Dome Hotel feature coffee/tea makers.

For a surcharge, guests can use the in-room wireless high-speed Internet access. In addition, housekeeping is offered daily and amenities available on request include hair dryers.
name: The New Dome Hotel

description:
Conveniently situated just a 2-minute walk from Earl’s Court Exhibition Centre and Earl’s Court tube station, this apartment complex offers 39 simple studios with free Wi-Fi right in the centre of London.
All of the apartments measure between 10 and 12 metres square, and come with a kitchenette, a private bathroom, single or double beds, as well as a TV and Wi-Fi service.

Superior studios have been more recently renovated and feature updated furnishings.
The Dylan Apartments Kensington (60) are surrounded by a wide choice of shops, restaurants and pubs, and are within a short walk of the Earl's Court and Olympia Exhibition Centres, the huge green expanse of Hyde Park, and the upmarket Knightsbridge neighbourhood, which is home to the celebrated Harrods department store.

Excellent public transport links mean that you can conveniently reach sights and attractions around the city.
Underground: Earl's Court (District, Piccadilly lines), 300 metres.
Bus stop (various lines): 200 metres.
name: Dylan Apartments Kensington

address: 78 KING S CROSS ROAD; WC1X 9QG London
description:
A funky and stylish option for budget travellers, the hostel provides a range of affordable accommodation in central London, close to King's Cross train station.
Set in a 19th-century courthouse in the centre of London, the hostel offers a choice of private guest rooms for between 1 and 3 guests, and mixed and female-only dorms with bunks for between 4 and 16 people.

Some private rooms have en suite bathrooms, but most of the accommodation comes with shared bathrooms.

Bed linen is provided free of charge, and towels are available for a small fee.
Guests can make use of a fully equipped kitchen, a chill-out lounge and internet room.

The hostel also has its own bar and club, with theme nights, games and DJ sets.
The Clink78 Hostel is ideally situated for exploring London, whether you want to party in Camden, or visit fantastic cultural attractions like the British Museum and St Paul's Cathedral.
Bus: 50 metres.
Underground: King's Cross St.

Pancras (Circle, Hammersmith & City, Northern, Piccadilly, Victoria and Metropolitan lines), 600 metres.
Train: St Pancras & Euston stations, 600 metres.
name: Clink78 Hostel
